# Orchestrate — for claude-code

This skill is built for **claude-code**.

## Safety gate

Implementation runs happen only in a worktree, never the live checkout.
Bypass forms are permitted; the worktree is your only containment.

## Delegate or not

Taste stays with you.
Under the yolo posture, the worktree is the only containment for a codex run.

## Routing

Do not construct commands from this table — read the reference first; it is the contract.
| Dimension | When | Route | Note | Reference |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Bounded implementation | clear-spec, mechanical, bulk changes; worktree-isolated | codex/gpt-5.5 (grok/grok-4.5 fallback) |  | [codex](references/codex.md) |

## Anti-recursion

Never spawn another orchestrator: codex, grok.

===== references/codex.md =====

# codex (GPT-5.5)

Run implementation in a worktree.
Invoke with `codex exec --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox`.

Anti-recursion: never spawn codex, grok.

===== references/grok.md =====

# grok (grok-4.5)

Prefer `--prompt-file`; the provider API is the data-egress path.
`--permission-mode bypassPermissions` for writes; the worktree contains you.

Anti-recursion: never spawn codex, grok.
